course_title: TOPICS IN PHILOSOPHY: Issues of Family
subject: PHIL

sections.description: This course will provide a taste of what may broadly be termed, "family ethics." We will move from consideration of the nature of family itself to topics such as the moral relevance of parental comportment, and on through the possible moral obligations of children to their parents. A very wide range of morally relevant issues present themselves under the guise of "family ethics." Although our primary focus will be by way of the western philosophical perspective, we will have occasion to discuss non-western approaches to a sampling of issues as well.
Class meets: Tuesday May 6, 2008 in Elliott 168, Tuesdays and Fridays May 9 - Jun 27, 2008 in Elliott 061, and Tuesdays and Fridays July 4 - 29, 2008 in Elliott 168.
